 inset), making it more difficult to reduce adhesion.
 On the other hand, a larger number hairs increases 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{max}$
\end_inset

, and is thus more favorable for reversible adhesion.
 This highlights the advantage of a split contact design of the adhesive
 pad to control adhesion by tilt.
 
